31:58.560 --> 32:01.060
What are you, nuts?

32:09.070 --> 32:11.615
After them! After them!

32:32.051 --> 32:34.344
- Why are we stopping here?
- We'II never outrun them,

32:34.345 --> 32:40.165
but we might be able to buy some time
with a Iittle camouflage.

32:42.896 --> 32:45.396
Duck down.

32:48.443 --> 32:50.943
Better stay down.

32:55.366 --> 32:57.451
Are you ever wrong about anything?

32:57.452 --> 33:00.371
Never. Well, once. Maybe twice.

33:00.538 --> 33:02.956
Once is all it takes to ruin your Iife.

33:02.957 --> 33:05.333
You're sure?
You're absolutely positive?

33:05.334 --> 33:07.844
They didn't come past here.

33:08.546 --> 33:12.507
I can't believe the man in that car
is the man I married.

33:12.508 --> 33:16.553
He told me he Ioved me
more than anything in the world.

33:16.554 --> 33:19.389
He made me feel
Iike I was worth something.

33:19.390 --> 33:22.475
You don't need him
to feel Iike that, do you?

33:22.476 --> 33:26.855
Let's face it, MacGyver, I'm about
as boring and generic as they come.

33:26.856 --> 33:31.443
I would feel right at home
dressed in a plain brown wrapper.

33:31.444 --> 33:33.486
What?

33:33.487 --> 33:36.614
Oh, I, I just had this image
of you dressed

33:36.615 --> 33:39.451
in a grocery bag, that's all. I'm sorry.

33:39.452 --> 33:42.172
They'd have to double-bag me.

33:46.584 --> 33:51.104
You're way too good for that guy.
You know that.

33:51.380 --> 33:53.880
Believe it.

33:58.053 --> 34:03.141
You two backtrack through this place
on foot. You get back to the front gate.

34:03.142 --> 34:05.894
You two, stay here.

34:16.196 --> 34:19.489
This should keep them
from spotting you for a while.

34:19.491 --> 34:22.034
You just never give up, do you?

34:22.034 --> 34:24.328
No, ma'am, I don't.

34:24.329 --> 34:25.996
The whole place is surrounded.

34:25.998 --> 34:27.415
Yeah.

34:27.416 --> 34:29.542
But I've got a plan.

34:29.543 --> 34:32.043
We're gonna have to signal
somebody on the outside.

34:32.045 --> 34:33.420
How are you gonna do that?

34:33.422 --> 34:34.797
I haven't figured that out yet.

34:34.797 --> 34:36.257
Great.

34:36.257 --> 34:40.219
Maybe one of those old boats
have got a flare gun in it.

34:40.219 --> 34:43.472
MacGyver, just in case
we don't get to

34:43.473 --> 34:45.391
breathe in the smog tomorrow,
I'd just--

34:45.391 --> 34:47.059
Hey.

34:47.060 --> 34:49.728
There's no forecast
for smog tomorrow.

34:49.730 --> 34:53.429
We're both gonna be around
to enjoy it.

34:56.194 --> 34:58.694
We will?

35:00.323 --> 35:05.293
Yeah, we have to.
I haven't gotten to go fishing yet.

36:01.801 --> 36:04.301
Not bad, MacGyver.

36:06.472 --> 36:08.682
But we've got bigger fish to catch.

36:08.683 --> 36:11.977
Listen, you're gonna have to be
as quiet as you possibly can.

36:11.978 --> 36:14.478
I'II come back for you.

36:14.981 --> 36:17.481
I promise.

37:03.863 --> 37:05.697
Good thing about boats:

37:05.698 --> 37:08.992
Some of the stuff you find on them
work just as well on land

37:08.993 --> 37:11.493
as they do on sea.

37:14.081 --> 37:16.708
Finding a flare gun
would've been nice,

37:16.709 --> 37:19.989
but signal flags are almost as good.

37:20.379 --> 37:26.467
Each flag has a different pattern
which stands for a different letter.

37:26.468 --> 37:28.970
I could say a whole lot
with these flags,

37:28.971 --> 37:31.890
but just one word came to mind:

37:32.933 --> 37:35.433
"Help. "

37:41.191 --> 37:45.403
Now I just had to figure out a way
to get someone to see these flags.

37:45.404 --> 37:47.904
The right someone.

37:57.499 --> 37:59.542
Sailboats have sails.

37:59.543 --> 38:02.670
What I needed was
the bag they came in.

38:02.671 --> 38:05.965
It was just the ticket
to get my message across.

38:05.966 --> 38:08.466
Or rather, up.

38:11.930 --> 38:15.975
The next step was finding something
to get it high enough to be seen.

38:15.976 --> 38:18.769
And I wasn't about to be picky.

38:18.770 --> 38:23.149
Desperation tends to make one
sort of flexible.

38:29.781 --> 38:34.891
Industrial gases.
One of those tanks might do the trick.

39:17.453 --> 39:19.953
Yo!

39:36.055 --> 39:38.890
Of all the gases available to me,

39:38.891 --> 39:43.937
the only one that would lift
the sail bag was in this tank.

39:43.938 --> 39:46.438
Or this tank.

39:51.278 --> 39:53.738
I still had one problem, though,

39:53.739 --> 39:56.991
but that water
might help me solve it.

39:56.992 --> 40:00.203
Helium molecules
are the smallest of all gases.

40:00.204 --> 40:01.955
They'd slip through
the sail-bag weave

40:01.956 --> 40:04.874
Iike smoke
through a window screen.

40:04.875 --> 40:08.419
By soaking the bag,
the surface tension of the water

40:08.420 --> 40:11.990
could plug up the holes
in the fabric.

40:22.059 --> 40:25.354
One helium balloon coming up.

40:46.750 --> 40:49.503
Oh, hurry, MacGyver.

41:29.251 --> 41:31.669
I knew Harryman's boys
would see the balloon and the flags.

41:31.670 --> 41:33.671
I'd have to deal with that.

41:33.672 --> 41:36.465
But I hoped someone else
would see them too.

41:36.466 --> 41:40.596
Someone who could
figure out what they meant.

41:48.812 --> 41:51.312
What the...?

41:53.149 --> 41:55.649
You guys stay here.

43:46.220 --> 43:48.262
Look at the balloon and flag
on the factory.

43:48.263 --> 43:51.493
Must be some kids
monkeying around.

43:53.393 --> 43:55.893
Hand me the binoculars.

44:06.615 --> 44:08.908
No kids put that together.

44:08.909 --> 44:10.951
Call headquarters.
Have them roll some backup.

44:10.952 --> 44:13.079
Those signal flags say
somebody needs help.

44:13.080 --> 44:14.663
How do you know that?

44:14.664 --> 44:16.874
Four years in the Navy
is how I know that.

44:16.875 --> 44:18.876
- Call them.
- Five Adam 16.

44:18.877 --> 44:21.377
Five Adam 16, reporting.

44:26.885 --> 44:28.969
Sorry to have to do this.

44:28.970 --> 44:31.470
I really am.

44:31.640 --> 44:34.140
No, you're not.

44:34.809 --> 44:36.727
It took me too Iong to realize,

44:36.728 --> 44:40.397
but I know now you're incapable of
feeling sorry for anything you've done.

44:40.398 --> 44:43.609
BIeeding hearts, you're all the same.

44:43.610 --> 44:46.737
Did you really think I was capable
of falling for someone Iike you?

44:46.738 --> 44:51.498
Yes, I did. I guess because
I needed to believe it.

44:51.576 --> 44:54.076
But you know what?

44:54.162 --> 44:56.371
You're the Ioser. Not me.

44:56.372 --> 44:57.831
I know that now.

44:57.832 --> 45:01.902
So go ahead and do whatever
you have to do.

45:02.462 --> 45:04.546
Whatever you say.

45:04.547 --> 45:07.047
I wouldn't if I were you.

45:28.196 --> 45:31.186
- How you doing?
- I'm terrific.

45:33.117 --> 45:34.534
What? Now?

45:34.535 --> 45:37.035
Now.

46:00.353 --> 46:01.561
How is she?

46:01.562 --> 46:04.689
Both mother and daughter
are doing fine.

46:04.690 --> 46:06.816
Daughter? She had a girl?

46:06.817 --> 46:09.317
EIaine wants to see you.

46:23.000 --> 46:25.418
Hi.

46:25.419 --> 46:27.253
Hi.

46:27.254 --> 46:29.422
Well, you see?
She didn't exactly turn out to be

46:29.423 --> 46:32.383
the monster you thought she'd be.

46:32.384 --> 46:34.052
I know.

46:34.053 --> 46:36.553
That's what scares me.

46:39.224 --> 46:42.310
I suppose I could keep her
on a trial basis.

46:42.311 --> 46:44.951
You know, for a week or two?

46:45.773 --> 46:48.942
